Activity Name: Resto del fondo con strava del celular, me quedé sin batería en el reloj 😹

Description: 61'10 HM PB😼

Had a great year of training, racing, and figuring it all out. Sub-4 mile, All-ACC, US champs, a big cross country season, and a ton of PR’s and experiences I had only dreamed of. Excited to put what I’ve learned all together and to keep dreaming in 2024!

2022 -> 2023
800m: 1:49.36 -> 1:47.25
Mile: 4:13.31 -> 3:59.96
8K XC: 25:44 -> 24:34
10K XC: 32:29 -> 31:05

Hi I ran 2:20.45 in a 1K which I am very happy with but got the collegiate record dropped on my head by a true freshman and beat by a bunch of other college kids which I am not very happy with but we are amidst some hard training and no one cares about being fast in January so we keep going!
After this I ran 2100m of the 3K in like 5:50 and it felt really easy 😁
Idk when I will race again but this was a lot of fun!

Yay for another sub-4! Felt solid! Stayed right on pace and closed in a 57. Shoutout to Matt with the world indoor standard and the VT boys joining the club. Really special to be a part of this
Paced Cole and Cooper through 600m of their 1000m in 1:23 shortly after this which was really fun!

Long run with the Lipscomb boys
Ran 1:18 for 600m and 1:48 for 800m this weekend. Gotta get better but it’s a good start for the training I’ve been doing. Heading to Albuquerque for USA indoors soon!

Activity Name: I ran 1:48 at altitude at USA’s and missed the final by 0.13
Description: Matt and I drove to a Native American preservation for a long run and then we got a ride back to our van in the back of a cop car for trespassing on federal land during a indigenous ceremony 😃😃😃 avoided 6 months in prison for good behavior! Hocker US Champ! See you in a few months after I start doing some mid-distance training!
3:41.98 for 2nd. Outdoor opener, plan was last lap fast lap. Let Nick out on the pacer and couldn’t chase him down. Good start for sure. Will get a chance to rip another one later
With Cooper and Rachel. Racing an 800m tonight, excited to see where my fitness is!

1:47.98 (53.46, 54.53) for 4th in the heat, 10th overall. Great weather, fast track, very solid meet to be a part of in April. Just not quite at this level yet. Out in the back as always, had a really solid middle 400m and thought I was bridging up to the leaders well, but then had absolutely nothing the last 150m. Been doing what I can with 5K training thus far, ready to flip to switch and get into 800m specific training. Definitely wanted more from this but we still have plenty of time. I’m a first 200m and last 200m away from something great
Came back to pace 1K of a 1500m in 2:27 later

Been off the grid for a while. Gave myself 3 shots at the Olympic Trials last week, running 1:47.3, 1:47.6, and 1:48.2 in a span of 8 days but was not enough to make it. Racing the World Athletics silver label Harry Jerome Classic 1500m tonight in a solid field. Been struggling a bit this year so will reset and train for about a month before getting back into some more fun races. Let me know of any track races or road miles I should hit up this summer!
Most fun I’ve had in a while. Just wanted to race and win the second pack. 4:18 for 7th
3:53.18 on a downhill course. Getting some practice in before some more downhill road races coming up!
3:54 for 4th! Such a fun event! Pushed the pace in the middle, happy with how it went. Huge, loud crowd last quarter mile. Definitely wanna come back next year!
Workout tomorrow
Going to try to get back into cycling for cross training a bit, miss all the rides I was doing a few years ago

24:56 for 10th. Hopped into this race after a few weeks of training because I would choose this over a few hard days of BT workouts anytime. Would love to race something long again in a few weeks when I’m more in shape. Felt really good the first half with the leaders then slowly faded second half
Lost my big ring on the way back
Or something like that
The most anticipated race of the year. I am unbelievably bad at running our course

Really pleased with this one. It’s been a hell of a last 12 months for me in about every way possible, so to come out here and finish top 10 feels like a win. It’s such an unparalleled feeling to give back to the people who’ve poured themselves into supporting you on race day.
Treadmill. Did some light strides toward the end to get the body moving a bit, felt halfway decent

First short run after the marathon always feels awful, but seems to jumpstart the recovery process for me. Fun to be back at practice and see the team after almost 3 weeks apart. Some big races at BU for the crew this weekend!
First workout back, dawgs are barkin’
Chilly morning. Wickets after 🏎️💨
6xMile 5:50-5:30, helping out Savannah and Katie. Muddy day at Davidson Mesa but a strong day for TME.
An old Drake workout, just a lot faster than I used to run it. 2 mile tempo in 10:12, 1200s in 3:27 down to 3:19 with 400m jog rest. Some :20 strides after to turn things over.
Legs a lil tired after skiing all weekend, but otherwise no worse for wear. 3:14 down to 3:00 with :60 jog rest between reps.
3:05 down to 2:51, good “speed” day for me especially solo and from the house.
5 miles in 24:40, 1-2-3-2-1 at 4:15-4:30 pace with equal float rest
Was supposed to be 6x2K, but the hotel gym circuit blew in the middle of rep 3, so had a nice 18 minute break while maintenance reset it. 2Ks were 6:15 down to 6:00, Ks were 3:00, 2:51.
7:00–>5:10 on the treadmill.

Wind and suffering. 30mph gusts at the track made for an absolute doozy. 1 warm up K at 3:07 then 4xK at 5K (2:50-2:47). Had to pivot to 300s because hitting pace was comically difficult. 300s were all right around 47. Good mental win day, was ready to call it and go home after the first rep.
Caved to peer pressure. Ks were 3:05-2:59 off :60 jog. 400s this afternoon.
Organized chaos, felt like we were calling an audible on the route every mile but somehow ended up being a perfect 17 mile loop. Nice to be back home and with the team!
Fun to send off Charlie, Chris and Josie! No marathon race for me tomorrow, but starting to feel the energy of Boston pick up.

Fun! Was with the pack through 2 miles, then Drew ran a 4:10 3rd mile and left me in the dust. Haven’t raced a 5K since 2020, so this was a bit of a shock to the system but in a good way. Nice way to kick off a full weekend with TCS and get a little tuneup effort in ahead of Road to Records 10K in two weeks.
With Drew Hunter this time!
With Joey and Drew. Miles were 5:00 down to 4:49, 400s were 67 down to 64. Tuned up and flying out to Germany tonight.
7 mile tempo at 5:02 pace, 6x:30 strides at ~4:30 pace. Beautiful weather today, and legs felt nice and poppy.
Post-lift

6:15 down to 5:50, basically just cutting down a second per lap per rep. Then some rhythm 200s in 31-33 with 200m jog. Legs were a bit fatigued with the turnaround from Monday, but a good solo session!
Perfect morning for a run, dare I say. Haven’t ran Big Dry Creek in quite a while, it’s a good one!
3:06 down to 2:50 off ~:60-:75 jog, 200s in :31 with a cheeky lil tailwind. Got the call up to the Pro Race for BolderBoulder on Monday! Pumped.
10:15➡️9:25 with ~3:00 jog rest. Tough day, but a good day! It’s been fun to be hitting faster paces in training more often. I’m a sore boy for it, but a fit boy for it.
Tired after yesterday. Not much soreness, just flat legs.

So much fun out there, thanks to everyone for showing Team USA and me some love. Racing a 10K at 5,300’ is still no joke, but is still worth it. Few events come close to the atmosphere of finishing in Folsom Field.

Solid day out. Basically acted as a pacer through mile 8, locked in to 4:40 pace, then the winner (61:13 guy earlier this year) hammered 8-9 and put about :10 into me and maintained that gap to the finish. Close to the title defense! And nice to sub sub-62. But would’ve loved to have hammered the last 5K a bit, but so it goes. On to summer vacation 😎
2Ks in 6:15, 6:00, 1K in 2:54, 800m in 2:05. Short and sweet little tuneup ahead of Chicago 13.1 on Sunday!
A little bridge day between the lab testing on Friday and the tuneup on Wednesday. Starting to get toasty in the mornings!
Nice run along the coastal cliffs with Christine.
Just a little movement to get some bloodflow post-race.
4 miles in 27:53 in honor of Drew Hunter’s 4th place finish in 27:53 at the Olympic Trials last night. Seems he’s a bit fitter than I am.
Machu Picchu tomorrow!
8x:20 on/:40 off strides. First fast running since Chicago 13.1, always a treat.
Warm morning. Who is AMillz?
2x8’, 1x4’ at tempo effort with Drew, Sam, Anthony.

Activity Name: Easy ➡️ Pacing Christine ➡️ Strides ➡️ Pacing Christine ➡️ Easy
Description: First workout of the build for Christine, she crushed it!
Long(er) run with Drew and Joey
Marathon szn approaching
30 Easy, 35 Moderate, 15 Uptempo. A little intro to marathon work again. 12 weeks and 1 day till Chicago!

A classic if ever there was one. Hovered around 5:10-5:15 for most of this, lactate testing after reps 2, 4, and 6. Always honest running on Big Dry Creek, it’s nice to come here early in a training block to just run to feel vs. trying to run flashy splits.
90° at the end. 8:30am practice is SO out for the rest of the summer.
Fun day with Drew, Sam, and Connor. Seven years later!
Back on the “quality in the long run” horse. Felt pretty solid for the first one of the build. 30 minutes easy, 30 minutes moderate, then 7 miles at 5:09 avg.
5:06, 5:07, 5:00 off :90 jog. Just a little double workout.
A classic. :60 jog between reps. A little second session this evening.

Happy with this after a big week. Moved on Wednesday, Double T Thursday, travelled yesterday, solid LR today. Crazy muggy and warm here, but good practice for Chicago with the climate and the long, straight stretches to shut the mind off.
Frank Lara stole some of my Westminster crowns so I was running off pure anger for this. Thanks to Drew Hunter for hanging out for a few reps.

A peaceful run for my last day as a Westminster resident. I’ll miss this route, but excited to make the move towards our community in Longmont. Grateful for our time here! On a closely related note, if anyone is looking to buy or rent a house in Westminster, slide into the Strava DMs 🤝
10:15, 10:00, 9:50 with 800m float rest at ~6:00, then 4:45 for the final mile. Legs a bit flat today after the LR—must be training for a marathon!
Bumped into Tony at mile 5. Ran 5-10 with him, then did the minute reps back out on Lefthand. All 4:40-4:45ish, minute jog rest between.
First workout here, nice spot. Soft surface but good footing. Reps were 6:28 down to 6:05. Feeling expectedly tired after the travel to and from MN.
77° dew point, 97% humidity. Thick as thick gets!

Activity Name: Long w/ 4 mi. Tempo + 4x(800m on/800m float)
Description: Legs felt really poppy coming off Monday’s race! Wasn’t sure how I’d feel for this, but coach and I wanted to do some faster running toward the end. Tempo was at 5:10 pace, 800s on 4:40-4:30 pace, floats in 6:00ish. Was pleasantly surprising to find that none of this really felt hard. FloTrack in town to film, video soon(ish).
11.5 total, pouring rain for the last 1.5

Tired legs! Lead pack took the first few miles out in mid-4:30s, which was too quick too early for me at this point in the Chicago build. Let them go thinking they’d come back to me in the last 5K, but ended up running solo from mile 5 to the finish. Good mental grind ahead of the full next month.
Nice to get in a strong effort today, beautiful weather. With Connor through 17.5, then did a 3 mile race pace pickup. All in Supernova Prima, good shoe!
6 miles at 5:35 to put some junk in the legs, then 3xMile in 4:34, 4:32, 4:31 with 3:00 jog rest between reps. Almost stole a rare Joe Klecker crown, I’ll have to lean at the line next time.
5:06 on the first loop, 5:02 on the second loop, 4:59 on the third loop, 4:52 on the fourth loop. Great mental prep for Chicago. Bit breezy, bit lonely, bit fatigued, but got it all done.
3:04 down to 2:48 with minute jog at about 6:30 pace between reps. A fun day! Haven’t ran much faster than 4:50 pace during the build, so it was good to turn over a bit.
5:09, 5:03, 4:56 pace with 2 minute jog between reps. Weather’s starting to turn, I’m about it.
With Charlie, 5:15ish for the tempo. Legs woke up nicely after the first mile.
Nothing like a good 5K at altitude during a marathon block to shock the system. 7th overall, fended off a fierce kick from Anthony Camerieri.
A strong close for fourth.
On sweeper bike duties, then sweeper walk duties. Go Bulldogs 🐶
5:05–>4:39 with :90 float rest between reps. On the dirt. Coach said to push the last rep.
6:10 down to 5:52 for the 2Ks, 4:25-4:15 pace for the minute reps. Textbook “I don’t want to be doing this but it feels good” taper workout.

Can’t argue with a :40 personal best! Proud of the way I raced, moved up from probably about 20th to 13th and 5th American to 3rd American in the second half. I thought closer to 2:09 was in the cards today, but it seemed to be a slower day than I think a lot of us expected based on how I moved up. I’ll take the progress, 2:0X 🔜
Race time.
Last little effort before Chicago. 3 miles at marathon rhythm, hard 800. Almost go time!
Race week!

Easy 8 with some strides in there. Watched the team run their 2K reps. Nice morning.
